[src:spectral-methods/spectral-method] Because a spectral element method is a finite element method of very high order, there is a similarity in the convergence properties.
[src:spectral-methods/spectral-method] However, whereas the spectral method is based on the eigendecomposition of the particular boundary value problem, the finite element method does not use that information and works for arbitrary elliptic boundary value problems.
